      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.13707v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        In classical Iwasawa theory, we mainly study codimension one behavior of arithmetic modules. Relatively recently, F. M. Bleher, T. Chinburg, R. Greenberg, M. Kakde, G. Pappas, R. Sharifi, and M. J. Taylor started studying higher codimension behavior of unramified Iwasawa modules which are conjectured to be pseudo-null. In this paper, by developing a general <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> theory on perfect complexes, we obtain a new perspective of their works. That allows us to extend the results to equivariant settings and, even in non-equivariant settings, to obtain more refined results concerning the higher codimension behavior.
