    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Covering dimension of Cuntz semigroups II
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Thiel%2C+H">Hannes Thiel</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Vilalta%2C+E">Eduard Vilalta</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.13062v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We show that the dimension of the Cuntz semigroup of a C*-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> is determined by the dimensions of the Cuntz semigroups of its separable sub-C*-&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.13062v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.13062v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.13062v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        We show that the dimension of the Cuntz semigroup of a C*-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> is determined by the dimensions of the Cuntz semigroups of its separable sub-C*-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebras</span>. This allows us to remove separability assumptions from previous results on the dimension of Cuntz semigroups.
  To obtain these results, we introduce a notion of approximation for abstract Cuntz semigroups that is compatible with the approximation of a C*-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> by sub-C*-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebras</span>. We show that many properties for Cuntz semigroups are preserved by approximation and satisfy a Löwenheim-Skolem condition.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.13062v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.13062v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
