      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.12493v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We give an algorithm to determine whether a kernel sheaf over a smooth projective curve over an <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraically</span> closed field is semistable. The algorithm uses symmetric powers to make destabilizing subbundles visible as global sections.
        
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.12493v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        We give an algorithm to determine whether a kernel sheaf over a smooth projective curve over an <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraically</span> closed field is semistable. The algorithm uses symmetric powers to make destabilizing subbundles visible as global sections.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.12493v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.12493v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
