    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        A Hecke <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> isomorphism over close local fields
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Ganapathy%2C+R">Radhika Ganapathy</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.12363v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;, the Hecke <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebras</span> $\mathcal{H}(G(F),K_m)$ and $\mathcal{H}(G(F&#39;),K_m&#39;)$ are isomorphic, where $K_m&#39;$ denotes the corresponding object over $F&#39;$. In this article, we generalize this result to general connected reductive groups.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.12363v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.12363v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.12363v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        Let $G$ be a split connected reductive group over $\mathbb{Z}$. Let $F$ be a non-archimedean local field. With $K_m: = Ker(G(\mathfrak{O}_F) \rightarrow G(\mathfrak{O}_F/\mathfrak{p}_F^m))$, Kazhdan proved that for a field $F&#39;$sufficiently close local field to $F$, the Hecke <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebras</span> $\mathcal{H}(G(F),K_m)$ and $\mathcal{H}(G(F&#39;),K_m&#39;)$ are isomorphic, where $K_m&#39;$ denotes the corresponding object over $F&#39;$. In this article, we generalize this result to general connected reductive groups.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.12363v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.12363v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 23 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
