    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Existence of birational small CM modules over biquadratic extensions in mixed characteristic
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Sridhar%2C+P">Prashanth Sridhar</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.12023v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        Let $S$ be an unramified regular local ring of mixed characteristic two and $R$ the integral closure of $S$ in a biquadratic extension of its quotient field obtained by adjoining roots of sufficiently general square free elements $f,g\in S$. Let $S^2$ denote the subring of $S$ obtained by lifting to $S$ the image of the Frobenius map on $S/2S$. When at least one of $f,g\in S^2$, we characterize th&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.12023v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.12023v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.12023v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        Let $S$ be an unramified regular local ring of mixed characteristic two and $R$ the integral closure of $S$ in a biquadratic extension of its quotient field obtained by adjoining roots of sufficiently general square free elements $f,g\in S$. Let $S^2$ denote the subring of $S$ obtained by lifting to $S$ the image of the Frobenius map on $S/2S$. When at least one of $f,g\in S^2$, we characterize the Cohen-Macaulayness of $R$ and show that $R$ admits a birational small Cohen-Macaulay module. It is noted that $R$ is not automatically Cohen-Macaulay in case $f,g\in S^2$ or if $f,g\notin S^2$.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.12023v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.12023v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 22 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    
