    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11975v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;there are finitely many relative equilibria (uniformly rotating configurations) and collapse configurations, except perhaps if the vorticities satisfy some explicitly given <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> constraints. In particular, if the vorticities are of the same sign, we show the number of relative equilibria and collapse configurations are finite.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11975v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.11975v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11975v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        For the planar five-vortex problem, we show that there are finitely many relative equilibria (uniformly rotating configurations) and collapse configurations, except perhaps if the vorticities satisfy some explicitly given <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> constraints. In particular, if the vorticities are of the same sign, we show the number of relative equilibria and collapse configurations are finite.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11975v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.11975v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

