    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Properties of Breuil-Kisin modules inherited by $p$-divisible groups
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Shaikh%2C+A+A">Absos Ali Shaikh</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Sarkar%2C+M+A">Mabud Ali Sarkar</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11837v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> $\mathscr{R}$ on a $p$-divisible group $\mathcal{G}$ defined over the ring of $p$-adic integers $\mathscr{O}_K$, we have constructed a new Breuil-Kisin module $\mathfrak{M}$ defined over the ring $\mathfrak{S}:=W(κ)[[u]]$ and studied freeness and projectiveness properties of such a module. Finally we have lifted the Breuil-Kisin module to étale leve&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11837v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.11837v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11837v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        In this paper, by assuming a faithful action of a finite flat $\mathbb{Z}_p$-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> $\mathscr{R}$ on a $p$-divisible group $\mathcal{G}$ defined over the ring of $p$-adic integers $\mathscr{O}_K$, we have constructed a new Breuil-Kisin module $\mathfrak{M}$ defined over the ring $\mathfrak{S}:=W(κ)[[u]]$ and studied freeness and projectiveness properties of such a module. Finally we have lifted the Breuil-Kisin module to étale level following the $\mathscr{R}$-action and showed that if the $p$-adic Tate module of a $p$-divisible group $\mathcal{G}$ over $\mathscr{O}_K$ is free then the corresponding lifted Breuil-Kisin module is free.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11837v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.11837v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 18 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    
