      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11301v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        In this paper, we derive the large-time profile of solutions to the Cauchy problem of a hyperbolic-parabolic system modeling the vasculogenesis in $\R^3$. When the initial data are prescribed in the vicinity of a constant ground state, by constructing a time-frequency Lyapunov functional and employing the Fourier energy method and spectral analysis, we show that solution of the Cauchy problem tend time-asymptotically to linear diffusion waves around the constant ground state with <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> decaying rates under certain conditions on the density-dependent pressure function.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11301v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.11301v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
